Quote:  The testimony that Moa bones have been found lying loose amongst the grass on the shingle of the [Canterbury] plains, together with small heaps of so-called Moa stones where probably a bird died & decayed, is too strong to be set aside altogether,....<i>Ibid.</i> 72 In the caves of Collingwood, all the moa stones are derived from the quartz ranges close by.
