Date:  0/0/1893
Source:  TrNZI
Author:
Vol / Page:  25/27
Edition:
Quote:  To aid in the digestion of this food, the moa, like many other birds, swallowed little pebbles, which, rounded & polished by the fricton of their stomach, assumed a peculiar form, and are called to this day `moa-stones' by the natives, who are familiar with them. [Hochstetter, 186].
Notes:   (De Guatrefages, trans L. Buller)

